org.morphus

Class MoConfig.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.morphus.MoConfig.Builder
  • Enclosing class:
    MoConfig

    public static final class MoConfig.Builder
extends Object
    Builder class to create MoConfig instance. Create an instance of this class by calling the constructor, and passing in the application context. Set up all the paremeters that you want to configure and call the create() method to create a MoConfig object.

      • setScreenZ

        public MoConfig.Builder setScreenZ(float screenZ)
        Sets z value of the view projection plane in world coordinates. Any object with z greater than the screen z will seem to go "inside" the screen and every object with a z smaller than the screen z will seem to pop out of the screen

      • setDeviceId

        public MoConfig.Builder setDeviceId(String deviceId)
        Device ID used by default is @android.provider.Settings.Secure.ANDROID_ID. In most instances this should work, but if your application uses another ID to identify this device, please override the value. Its important to note that although its called a deviceID, in reality, it can be any unique identifier that can be used to identify your application. The ID should ideally be stable across launches of applications (and possibly remove-install cycles of an application).
        Parameters:
        deviceId - unique device id.
